name: Chip Supply
overview: Chip Supply, Inc. distributes and processes semiconductor die and specialized packaging solutions for military, space, medical, commercial, and industrial applications in the United States. It offers wafer processing and die products, such as die distribution, wafer saw, bare die inspection, thinning/backgrinding, wafer bumping, and carrier options; packaging solutions, including hermetic packaging/QML, chip scale packaging, WLCSP/bumping, multi chip packaging, and tape automated bond products; and die banking, life-cycle planning, IC counterfeiting, and PCN/ECN products. The company also provides element evaluation/lot acceptance testing, wafer probe, test and product engineering, burn-in and environmental screening, SEM w/EDX, programming, and failure analysis services. Chip Supply, Inc. was founded in 1978 and is based in Orlando, Florida.
